Description: Sherd of body of pottery closed vessel, perhaps a table amphora. On neck 'perspective' maeander band in black, red and probably white, between white lines; at top of shoulder, frieze of opposed wave pattern; traces of decoration below. Dark brown Nile silt fabric.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IC.050)
